title: Ask HN: Tips for using OpenAI’s lower end models
text:
I’ve struggled to get good results from openai’s lower cost models like Curie, Babbage, and Ada.

Does anyone have tips or tricks to squeeze the most performance out of these? Or specific tasks that they are able to excel at?

title: Ask HN: What is the best way to Layoff in a small team?
text:
We have a situation. We are a small team of 4-5 people. We have a person who is clearly not a great fit. As a tech lead, I have never fired a person before. What is the best way to do that?

What are some Pre and Post steps? Esp. with the current economic situation, how would it be perceived by everyone else in the small team?

title: Ask HN: Which photographers do you admire?
text: Everyone has a genre of photography that they like the best. In your specific genre, which photographers are you inspired by and what do they photograph?

Show HN: The fastest way to test business ideas and collect early users
text:
Last year, I launched a Side Project (as an Indie Hacker) but didn't make any sales at all. I spent dollars without having even one customer. I made $0 (profit).

From that pain, I learn something: It's always better to validate an idea before jumping into coding (I spent at least 3 months building a project that would ruin my entire year).

Hence, I decided to keep building SaaS, but with a new approach: before working on the upcoming SaaS ideas, I wanted to have an easy-and-fast way of having a landing page that helps to collect early signups…

Last week, I launched EarlyAccess.to help founders accelerate the process of validating Business ideas and collecting early users/customers.
